.SH OPTIONS
This program follows the usual GNU command line syntax, with long
options starting with two dashes (`-').
However, currently
.B pico-test 
doesn't accept any options or parameters.
.SH EXAMPLES
Use of 
.B pico-test 
is pretty basic.
.TP
.B pico-test
Perform a test authentication. A QR code will be sent to 
.BR stdout (3), 
and the authentication log output will be sent to 
.BR syslog (3).
